This is commercial, proprietary software. Its source code is published so
that anyone can verify what Enclave.host actually runs: the platform's chain
of trust lets you check that the enclave images serving enclave.host were
built from the exact commits published in this repository. Publication here
is for transparency, audit and verification — it does not make this software
open source, and no rights are granted except those below.

1. PERMITTED USES

Subject to the restrictions in section 2, you may, free of charge:

  a. View, clone and fork this repository for the purpose of reading,
     reviewing and auditing the code.

  b. Build and run the software locally, in non-production settings, solely
     to audit it, to reproduce published release artifacts and attestation
     measurements, or to verify that the deployed Enclave.host service
     matches this source.

  c. Build and use the client components — the `cli/` directory, the install
     scripts, and code samples in the documentation — to interact with the
     hosted Enclave.host service.

  d. Perform good-faith security research against your own local builds, and
     publish or report your findings (responsible disclosure of
     vulnerabilities affecting the live service is appreciated).

